    {
      "id": "graph-contract-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "position": {
        "x": 740,
        "y": -180
      },
      "width": 660,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Core Rule\n\nA `.node` artifact becomes a **graph** when it contains one authority-bearing **declaration** node.\n\nThat declaration is the minimum graph contract and the first authoritative interpretation point.\n\nIt should state:\n- graph identity\n- authority and mutation policy\n- dependencies and settings\n- what primary artifact or surface the graph exposes\n- which node-view and editor-view are primary, if any\n\n## Boundary\n\nTemplate requirements are separate. A template may require more than the minimum graph, but those extra rules do not define graph-ness.\n\n## Compatibility\n\n`manifest` may still be read for older graphs, but it is compatibility-only and should not be created in new templates.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "graph-contract-shape",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Minimum Shape",
      "position": {
        "x": 740,
        "y": 250
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 460,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Minimum Shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"declaration\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"identity\": {},\n    \"authority\": {},\n    \"dependencies\": {},\n    \"settings\": {},\n    \"document\": {},\n    \"declaresKind\": \"graph\",\n    \"declaration\": {\n      \"kind\": \"graph\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Reading Rule\n\nReaders should interpret the graph through the declaration first, then read the remaining nodes in that light.\n\nThat gives one obvious starting point instead of splitting graph identity from graph declaration.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "graph-contract-template-boundary",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Template Boundary",
      "position": {
        "x": 1180,
        "y": 250
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 460,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Template Boundary\n\nA template is a graph with extra authoring intent and surface requirements.\n\nDo not use template requirements to decide whether a file is a graph.\n\nThe correct order is:\n1. decide whether the artifact is a graph\n2. decide whether it is also a template\n3. apply template-specific requirements only after graph validity is established\n\nThis keeps graph-ness separate from reuse-ness.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    }
  ],
